{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_appling_ver02/data/sn82007642/00279558194/1930102301/0763.xml":{"full_text":"OCTOBER 23, 1930\nLees-Mc\u00dfae Installs\nNew Student Council\nInstallation service for the offi\ncers of the Student Council of Lees-\nMc\u00dfae College was held Monday, Oc\ntober 13. Rev- W. R. Smith, director\nof religious activities, conducted the\nservice. After making a brief talk,\nMr. Smith charged Mr. Zimmerman\nas faculty advisor of the council who\nthen charged he members of the\ncouncil.\nThe council is composed of the\nfollowing students: President, George\nBaker; first vice-president, C- L.\nStucky; second vice-president, Rob\nert Hoss; secretary, Edith Robbins;\ntreasurer, Lloyd Blalock; president\n\u25a0of the senior college class. Otis Lon\ndon; president of junior college class\n\u25a0Gailen Willis; president of the sen\nior high school class, Mary Young;\npresident of the Junior High School\nclass, Robert Clothier; president of\nthe sophomore class, Jincy Winegar;\npresident of the freshman high\nschool class, Sam Lankford; senior\ncollege class representative, Kitty\nGuilfiams and Margaret Mozingo; ju\nnior college class representatives,\nFrances Morris; and day student rep\nresentative, Clyde Cooke-\nAfter the ceremony of installation\nthe student body rose and with up\nlifted hand pledged itself by an oath\nof allegiance to uphold the council\nin all things and to abide by its rul\nings. The service was concluded by\nsinging two stanzas of the school\nsong, \u201cAwav in the Beautiful Val\nley.\u201d\n451,740 AUTOS IN STATE\nA total of 451,740 motor vehicles\nwere registered in North Carolina on\nOctober 1, records of Sprague Sil\nver, head of the motor vehicle bu\nreau. disclosed.\nGuilford County led the State in\nthe number of vehicles listed with\n29.410.\nMecklenburg was next in line with\n27,255 and Forsyth was third with\n21,540-\nA small ccheck for $367.25 net\ncame to one farmer of Halifax Coun\nty iast week for 19 hogs which he\nfattened under the Shay system and\nshipped to the Richmond market-\nCOaAiO7V\nRADIO\nWITH TONE CONTROL\nModel 51\nR/jj $10999\nLESS TUBES\nRepresents the most we can\noffer you in radio satisfaction\nby any standard\nBeauty\nPerformance\nPrice\nWhen you hear CLARION\nRADIO in action you'll\nknow immediately that here\nis the radio yo\u00ab have been\nlooking (or.\nStop in and let CLARION\n\"speak for itself\"\u2014 or phone\norikat you would like to test\n6i*trafy remarkable receiver\nla year own home.\nOther Cl arrows are priced\nSJSCOOto WTfcOOWMbw.\nJ. L. GARWOOD\nPIANO COMPANY\nNORTH WILKESBORO, N. C.\nPinnacle Mills Flour At\nVery SPECIAL Prices!\nWe are now offering this leading brand of\nFlour\u2014good No. I grade at special prices\nthe lowest at which flour is to be found in\nBoone, quality considered.\nWe have a few bags of fertilizer left which\nwe are closing out at a big reduction.\nWe are offering top prices for\nPoultry and Eggs\nCASH FLOUR FEED COMPANY\nGEORGE V. McGIMSEY, Manager\nDepot Street Boone, N. C.\nSam Price Withdraws\nFrom Tennessee Race\nJohnson City, Tenn.\u2014Sam W.\nPrice has withdrawn from the Con\ngressional race in the First Tennes\nsee District- Following the August\nprimary, in which Price was defeat\ned by Carroll Reece, Price had an\nnounced that he \u201cwas still a candi\ndate,\u201d and had begun his campaign\nfor election. His withdrawal last\nnight \u201cafter mature deliberation,\u201d\nand after \u201cconsultation with some\nof my friends,\u201d was announced in a\nbrief statement in which he says \u201cI\nam convinced that it is best to yield\nthe point of personal privilege in the\ninterest of party harmony.\u201d He in\ndicated in his statement that he still\nmaintains a political interest which,\nas he stated, may persuade him to\n\u201ccome again.\u201d\nPrice\u2019s statement of withdrawal\nfollows:\n\u201c1 am withdrawing from the Con\ngressional race- My name will not\nappear upon the official ballot. This,\nis done reluctantly, but after mature\ndeliberation.\n\u201cThis campaign has gathered about\nme the finest ccrwd of personal and\npolitical friends any man ever had.\nI am proud of and deeply grateful\nto them.\n\u201cTo some of these my retirement\nwill be a sore disappointment. This\nI regret- However, it will do them\nno real harm and will save the polit\nical fortunes of others equally faith\nful and true. In this I can take pleas\nure.\n\u201c1 have long entertained the de\nsire to represent my district in Con\ngress. And I am still of the opinion\nthat I had a majority of the legal\nvotes cast in the August primary-\nPersonally, 1 should like to fight it\nout to a finish; but I am convinced\nthat it is best to yield the point of\npersonal privilege in the interest of\nparty harmony. I am convinced, also,\nthat my individual resources are not\nequal to that of the whole adminis\ntration.\n\u201cI am withdrawing from a race\nnational in its character in the hope\nthat my voluntary effaeement may\ncontribute in some measure to the\nticket and increase the chances of\na Republican victory in this State\nin the Presidential election two years\nhence.\n\u201cIn this course I have consulted\nsome of my friends that have stood\nby me loyally all through the cam\npaign.\u201d\nGardner Believes This\nA Democratic Year\nThis is a Democratic year, not\n(inly in North Carolina, but over the\nUnited States generally, Governor O.\nMax Gardner believes, so much so\nthat he predicts that Josiah William\nBailey, the Democratic candidate for\nthe United States Senate, will be vic\ntorious over his Republican oppon\nent, George M. Pritchard, by a ma\njority of from 75,000 to 100,000 in\nthe November election\nNot only have the people in North\nCarolina become disgusted with the\npresent Republican administration,\nbut the people all over the United\nStates have become disgusted with\nit, so that they are now turning to\nthe Democratic party as holding out\nthe only hope for relief,\u201d Governor\nGardner said. The bankers and busi\nness men over the nation have long\nsince lost confidence in the admin\nistration of President Hoover, for ev\nery time that Mr. Hoover or Secre\ntary of Commerce Lamont have pre\ndicted the return of prosperity, an\nother break has occurred in the stock\nmarket or something else has hap\npened to make the situation Worse\nthan it was before. Mr. Hoover or\nMr. Lamont have made these predic\ntions five different times and each\ntime things have sunk lower\nEven in Pennsylvania the Re\npublican Party is being split up with\ndissensions of all kinds so that the\nchances are excellent there for the\nelection of a Democrat as Governor.\nAnd even rock-ribbed Republican\nSenator Grundy, of high tariff fame,\ncalls attention to the fact that every\ntime Pennsylvania has elected a\nDemocratic Governor the nation has\nfollowed by electing a Democratic\nPresident. I am inclined to think\nSenator Grundy is correct and that\nnot only will Pensylvania have a\nDemocratic Governor this next time,\nbut that a Democratic President will\nbe elected in 1932.\u201d\nRays of the sun, concentrated bv\npassing through a fish bowl, set fire\nto the home of Dr. Morris Zimmer\nman, of Newark, N. J.\nTHE WATAUGA DEMOCRAT\u2014EVERY THURSDAY\u2014BOONE, N. C.\nBoone People\nare Recent\nVictims of\nFire!\nBeautiful and charming! It\u2019s an added special quality that makes the\nbeauty of a pretty girl. But she\u2019s a natural favorite to begin with. And\nfor the same reason Camels are favorites with the modern crowd.\nScientific principles govern their manufacture; but the mildness, the\nfragrance, the delicate flavor are natural qualities of the tobacco.\nThere\u2019s enjoyment in the smoking of a Camel. Camels go with\nhappy faces a lift of spirits with the opening of every fresh, fragrant\npack. For Camel\u2019s delightful mildness holds all the natural goodness of\nchoicest tobaccos. Don\u2019t confuse it with the flatness or insipidness of\n\u201cover-treated\u201d cigarettes.\n\u201cEASY TO LISTEN TO\u201d\u2014CAMEL PLEASURE HOUR\nWednesday evenings on N. B. C. network, WJZ and\nassociated stations. Consult your local radio time table. Tobacco Co., Winston-Salem, N. C.\nSeveral different fires have occurred in this vicinity re\ncently. One of the town\u2019s finest homes was destroyed this\nweek. It was insured, as were the preceding ones, and set\ntlements are being readily effected. Are you insured?\nAt this season, when the fires are first being huilt for heating purposes, the fire\nhazard is greatest- During the summer rats and mice have had a chance to work in\nthe plaster of your flues and with the first cold weather these defects which may ex\nist are likely to prove disastrous. Don\u2019t take the chance of losing your home or your\nbusiness house, and he without any means of starting the rebuilding thereof.\nWe represent the strongest British concerns doing business in this country, and\nall leading home companies, and can quote you exceedingly favorable rates on\nyour fire insurance requirements.\n\u201cBETTER BE SAFE THAN SORRY\u201d\nWatauga Insurance Company\nWatauga Bank Building BOONE, NORTH CAROLINA\nTHREE","height":"20231","width":"13923"}}
